result.formatted_address: 92 Siena Ave, Discovery Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: MooFish

reviews.text: Starter was very nice. Got the fish sandwich as the main which was pretty ordinary. Fish was second rate and tasted like it was fried in old Canola oil. Service was quick and friendly.
As expected for discovery bay, pricey meals. Service was good. Chow mein was delish however avoid the mac and cheese, very bland, no flavour at all. Even our child wouldn't touch it.
Great food, service and ambience. Very pleasant dining experience. I had the ribs, lobster roll and caramel pudding. Lovely!

Friendly service and good food. A good dining choice especially if you're in the DB North area. Prices tend to be on the higher side (since this is Discovery Bay after all), however the food is tasty. The outdoor seating with the sea in the backdrop provides an excellent and relaxing meal with friends or loved ones. Would recommend!
Coming every week or every 2 weeks. Never disappointed
